Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance of prequential plug-in codes in the context of one-parameter exponential families, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of the redundancy rates of different codes also involves concepts from data structures (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the comparison of different universal codes relates to complexity theory (cs.CC).
